title: Trio_Start
---
// Track which beasts have been calmed this fight. Declared once, reset every start
// (so a Try Again / fresh battle begins with all three still wild).
<<declare $leopard_calm = false>>
<<declare $lion_calm = false>>
<<declare $wolf_calm = false>>
<<set $leopard_calm = false>>
<<set $lion_calm = false>>
<<set $wolf_calm = false>>
The leopard, the lion and the she-wolf step from the wood together and ring you round. Three hungers, one road — and no way back.
<<fight_start>>
===


title: Trio_SootheLeopard
---
You turn to the restless leopard and fall into its darting rhythm, moving with it until the frenzy drains away.
<<fight_dodge "leopard_pounce">>
<<if fight_hp() <= 0>>
    <<fight_end "lose">>
<<else>>
    <<set $leopard_calm = true>>
    The leopard's circling slows; its curiosity is no longer a threat.
    <<jump Trio_AfterSoothe>>
<<endif>>
===


title: Trio_SootheLion
---
You lower your eyes before the lion and offer it no pride to fight.
<<fight_dodge "lion_charge">>
<<if fight_hp() <= 0>>
    <<fight_end "lose">>
<<else>>
    <<set $lion_calm = true>>
    The lion's roar fades to a watchful rumble.
    <<jump Trio_AfterSoothe>>
<<endif>>
===


title: Trio_SootheWolf
---
You meet the she-wolf's bottomless hunger with steady, unhurried resolve — wanting nothing she can take from you.
<<fight_dodge "wolf_snap">>
<<if fight_hp() <= 0>>
    <<fight_end "lose">>
<<else>>
    <<set $wolf_calm = true>>
    The she-wolf's snarl falters; for once, her hunger finds no purchase.
    <<jump Trio_AfterSoothe>>
<<endif>>
===


// Shared check after any beast is soothed. Unlocks Spare only when all three are calm.
title: Trio_AfterSoothe
---
<<if $leopard_calm and $lion_calm and $wolf_calm>>
    The three beasts circle once more, then settle as one. The road they guarded lies open.
    <<fight_spare_enable>>
<<else>>
    One beast is at peace — but the others still pace and snarl, waiting their turn.
<<endif>>
<<fight_menu>>
===


title: Trio_Win
---
Leopard, lion and she-wolf draw back together, and the dark wood parts to let you through at last.
===


title: Trio_Lose
---
Three hungers are too many for one road. The beasts close in, and the way is lost.
===
